00:34.709 --> 00:36.667
WELL, I AM AVOIDING
SAM'S KISSES.

00:36.709 --> 00:38.667
I'M AVOIDING DELL'S KISSES.

00:38.709 --> 00:40.667
I AM AVOIDING BEING KISSED.

00:40.709 --> 00:44.041
I'M GONNA DONATE MY LIPS
TO CHOCOLATE. (gasps)

00:44.083 --> 00:46.041
YEAH, WELL, THE COP
STILL HASN'T CALLED.

00:46.083 --> 00:47.250
TWO WEEKS, NO CALL.

00:47.291 --> 00:50.041
THESE LIPS? DRY.

00:50.083 --> 00:53.291
VIRGIN LIPS UNTOUCHED BY MAN.
(gasps)

00:53.333 --> 00:56.041
I AM HAVING SEX

00:56.083 --> 00:58.208
WITH BOTTEGA VENETA.

00:58.250 --> 01:00.208
I PUT MY HANDS INSIDE
A WOMAN'S BODY,

01:00.250 --> 01:02.208
AND I FIX WHAT'S WRONG.

01:02.250 --> 01:04.625
BUT EVERY WOMAN'S BODY
IS DIFFERENT.

01:04.667 --> 01:07.000
EVERY WOMAN'S STORY
IS DIFFERENT.

01:07.041 --> 01:09.041
WE GET OUR BONUS CHECKS
THIS WEEK,

01:09.083 --> 01:13.208
AND I SAY WE BLOW IT ALL
ON MNEMBA ISLAND.

01:13.250 --> 01:16.083
IT--IT'S ZANZIBAR, COOP.
IT'S UNSULLIED.

01:16.125 --> 01:18.083
LET'S GO SULLY IT.

01:18.125 --> 01:20.583
COOPER?

01:20.625 --> 01:22.041
ARE YOU LISTENING?

01:22.083 --> 01:24.625
I'M GONNA HAVE TO
CALL YOU BACK.

01:24.667 --> 01:26.000
HOW DO YOU KNOW

01:26.041 --> 01:28.667
YOU'RE DOING WHAT'S BEST
TO TAKE CARE OF YOUR CHILD?

01:28.709 --> 01:31.041
WHO'S GONNA HELP YOU
IF THE BABY WON'T EAT,

01:31.083 --> 01:33.041
ISN'T GAINING ENOUGH WEIGHT,
HAS A FEVER?

01:33.083 --> 01:34.667
THAT'S MY JOB.

01:34.709 --> 01:38.917
COME HERE TO ME... NOW.

01:38.959 --> 01:41.291
I USE EASTERN MEDICINE
TO PREVENT ILLNESS.

01:41.333 --> 01:44.041
I SOLVE PROBLEMS
BEFORE THEY START.

01:44.083 --> 01:46.625
SO I WAIT OUTSIDE ADDISON'S
HOUSE FOR, LIKE, 2 HOURS.

01:46.667 --> 01:48.083
SHE DIDN'T SHOW UP.

01:48.125 --> 01:50.083
I DON'T WAIT OUTSIDE
WOMEN'S HOUSES.

01:50.125 --> 01:52.208
SHE SHOULD BE WAITING
OUTSIDE MY HOUSE.
DOES SHE EVEN KNOW
YOU'RE INTERESTED?

01:52.250 --> 01:54.875
SHE'LL KNOW. I'M ON IT.
SHE HAS YOU ON A STRING.

01:54.917 --> 01:56.875
YEAH, YOU GET ANYWHERE
WITH NAOMI?

01:56.917 --> 01:58.875
HEY, THAT--THAT'S--
THAT'S NOT THE POINT.

01:58.917 --> 02:00.917
OKAY, I'M NOT ON A STRING.
PFFT.

02:00.959 --> 02:03.667
I'M IN CHARGE.
I'M--I'M IN CONTROL.

02:03.709 --> 02:05.041
I GOT THIS.

02:05.083 --> 02:08.166
YEAH, HOW DO YOU
HAVE THIS?

02:08.208 --> 02:10.917
I DON'T KNOW YET.

02:10.959 --> 02:12.917
A DOCTOR'S OFFICE
SHOULD BE A SANCTUARY.

02:12.959 --> 02:16.583
THE CARE YOU RECEIVE
SHOULD BE PERSONAL.
(Addison) IT'S GOOD.

02:16.625 --> 02:18.959
THAT'S WHAT WE DO.
WE'RE A FAMILY...
REALLY GOOD.
NAOMI DID A GOOD JOB.

02:19.000 --> 02:22.291
IT LOOKS LIKE IT COST WAY MORE
THAN SHE SAID IT WOULD COST.

02:22.333 --> 02:25.667
IS THIS GONNA AFFECT OUR BONUS
CHECKS? I NEED MY BONUS CHECK.
YOU'RE GONNA GET
YOUR BONUS CHECKS.

02:25.709 --> 02:28.041
WE SOUND PROFESSIONAL,
BUT IS IT JUST ME,

02:28.083 --> 02:31.917
OR IS IT A GAP AD
FOR MEDICINE?
YEAH, WE'RE BRANDED.
WE'RE A BRAND, LIKE A PERFUME.

02:31.959 --> 02:34.041
"MY SYMPTOMS"--
A FRAGRANCE FOR MEN.

02:34.083 --> 02:36.291
DELL, WHAT'D YOU THINK?
YOU CUT MY LINE.

02:36.333 --> 02:38.709
I WASN'T EVEN IN IT,
NOT ONE SINGLE SHOT OF ME.

02:38.750 --> 02:40.625
(Sam) YOUR WIFE'S...
(Pete) YOUR HUSBAND'S.

02:40.667 --> 02:42.583
AT OCEANSIDE WELLNESS...
OUR FAMILY

02:42.625 --> 02:44.041
TAKES CARE OF YOUR FAMILY.

02:44.083 --> 02:45.834
I REALLY NEED
MY BONUS CHECK, SAM.
YEAH, BONUS CHECK.

02:45.875 --> 02:47.834
(Pete) YEAH, SAM,
BONUS CHECKS.

02:47.875 --> 02:49.834
EVERYBODY'S GETTING
THEIR BONUS CHECKS.

02:49.875 --> 02:52.041
(sighs)
SHE'S AVOIDING ME.

02:52.083 --> 02:55.625
I'LL TALK TO HER.

02:55.667 --> 02:58.083
NAI,
THE VIDEO LOOKS GOOD.

02:58.125 --> 03:01.041
YEAH, IT'S, UH, UH,
GONNA RUN ON THE INTERNET,

03:01.083 --> 03:03.041
IN THE LOBBY
ON THE MONITORS,

03:03.083 --> 03:05.041
AND I ALSO LINED UP
A GROUP OF DENTISTS

03:05.083 --> 03:07.250
WHO ARE GONNA SHOW IT
IN THEIR OFFICES.

03:07.291 --> 03:10.041
IT COST A LOT OF MONEY, BUT YOU
SPEND MONEY TO MAKE MONEY.

03:10.083 --> 03:12.667
THAT'S THE GOAL--
MAKE MONEY.
YOU OKAY?

03:12.709 --> 03:14.667
YEAH, I'M FINE.
YOUR FILES...

03:14.709 --> 03:17.208
AND THESE.
THANK YOU, DELL.

03:17.250 --> 03:19.875
IF YOU HAVE SOME TIME LATER, I
THINK WE SHOULD HAVE A MEETING.

03:19.917 --> 03:21.542
I HAVE, UH,

03:21.583 --> 03:23.542
WALL-TO-WALL PATIENTS TODAY,
SO...

03:23.583 --> 03:25.000
OKAY.

03:29.083 --> 03:32.041
HE TRY TO KISS YOU AGAIN?
DID SAM?

03:32.083 --> 03:34.041
'CAUSE I'LL PUNCH 'EM.
VERBALLY, I MEAN.

03:34.083 --> 03:36.875
I CAN DO VERBAL PUNCHING FOR
YOU. I WOULD DO THAT FOR YOU.

03:36.917 --> 03:39.041
NAI, ARE YOU--WHAT'S WRONG?

03:39.083 --> 03:41.917
NOTHING, I AM FINE.
I'VE GOT PATIENTS.

03:46.041 --> 03:48.000
WHAT HAPPENED
TO THE PAPER CUPS?

03:48.041 --> 03:50.083
THEY'RE NOT JUSTIFIABLE
ENVIRONMENTALLY.
(elevator bell dings)

03:50.125 --> 03:53.250
MUGS--ARE THEY JUSTIFIABLE?
THE DISHWASHER.

03:53.291 --> 03:57.041
HEY, COOPER. GUESS WHO'S BEEN
TO THE TRAVEL AGENT.
OH.

03:57.083 --> 03:59.500
LOOK, ZANZIBAR. DON'T YOU
FEEL DRUNK JUST LOOKING AT IT?

03:59.542 --> 04:02.667
I DON'T KNOW IF I CAN
GO AWAY THIS YEAR.
WE GO AWAY EVERY YEAR.

04:02.709 --> 04:05.959
I HAVE A PATIENT.
WE'LL TALK ABOUT IT LATER.

04:08.208 --> 04:09.542
DR. KING.
DR. FREEDMAN.

04:09.583 --> 04:12.041
I ASSUME YOU'RE HERE ON
IMPORTANT HOSPITAL BUSINESS?

04:12.083 --> 04:14.917
I AM.
WELL, LET'S... TALK.

04:21.083 --> 04:23.667
♪♪

04:23.709 --> 04:25.667
CAN I TELL PEOPLE
ABOUT US?

04:25.709 --> 04:27.083
WHAT?
I MEAN, JUST VIOLET.

04:27.125 --> 04:30.083
IT'S GETTING SECRET-Y,
AND I DON'T REALLY DO SECRET-Y,

04:30.125 --> 04:32.083
AND MY BONUS CHECK COMES
THIS WEEK.

04:32.125 --> 04:34.667
YOU WANT TO PAY ME
FOR THE SEX?

04:34.709 --> 04:36.667
I THOUGHT WE COULD USE
THE MONEY

04:36.709 --> 04:38.542
TO GO AWAY TOGETHER...
ON VACATION.

04:38.583 --> 04:41.083
YOU AND ME ON A... VACATION?
YEAH, LIKE A NORMAL COUPLE.

04:41.125 --> 04:43.500
(music stops)

04:43.542 --> 04:45.250
I TELL VIOLET EVERYTHING.
SHE'S LIKE MY SISTER.

04:45.291 --> 04:47.250
SHE'S LIKE MY HOT SISTER,

04:47.291 --> 04:50.291
AND WE USE OUR BONUS CHECKS
TO GO AWAY EVERY YEAR.

04:50.333 --> 04:53.083
BUT I THINK IF I WENT AWAY
WITHOUT YOU--
DO NOT SAY IT.

04:53.125 --> 04:55.041
I MIGHT MISS YOU.
COOPER.

04:55.083 --> 04:58.041
YES.
EITHER GET BACK ON TOP OF ME
AND SHUT UP,

04:58.083 --> 05:01.792
OR KEEP TALKING AND WATCH ME
WALK OUT THAT DOOR.

05:01.834 --> 05:04.917
♪♪

05:10.959 --> 05:14.041
THERE IS A LACK
OF PAPER CUPS.
DELL'S GOING GREEN.

05:14.083 --> 05:17.041
SO WHAT ARE YOU DOING
WITH YOUR BONUS?
MAYBE BUYING PAPER CUPS.

05:17.083 --> 05:18.667
(chuckles)

05:18.709 --> 05:21.083
DO YOU WANT
TO GO OUT SOMETIME?
OUT?

05:21.125 --> 05:23.041
ON A DATE.

05:23.083 --> 05:24.625
WELL, THAT'S...

05:24.667 --> 05:27.834
UH... DO YOU THINK
THAT'S WISE?

05:27.875 --> 05:30.041
UH, IS THERE SOMEONE ELSE?

05:30.083 --> 05:32.083
YES. NO.

05:32.125 --> 05:35.166
THERE WAS A PERSON, UH,
AN OFFICER OF THE LAW,

05:35.208 --> 05:37.041
BUT WE NEVER CONNECTED.

05:37.083 --> 05:40.291
SO, NO, NO, THERE'S--
THERE'S NO ONE ELSE.
OKAY, THEN.

05:40.333 --> 05:42.583
THINK ABOUT IT.

05:53.250 --> 05:55.750
(knock on door)

05:55.792 --> 05:58.750
HEY, UH, MOLLY MADISON
IS ON HER WAY IN.
SHE WAS JUST HERE
A COUPLE OF DAYS AGO.

05:58.792 --> 06:00.208
I--OH, NERVOUS MOMMIES.

06:00.250 --> 06:02.750
I DO NOT HAVE TIME
FOR NERVOUS MOMMIES.

06:02.792 --> 06:05.041
HEY, ADDIE. CAN YOU SEE
A PATIENT FOR ME?

06:05.083 --> 06:06.250
SHE'S IN ROOM, UH...

06:06.291 --> 06:08.875
FOUR.
YEAH, I HAVE TIME.

06:08.917 --> 06:10.667
THANKS.
THANK YOU.

06:10.709 --> 06:12.041
WHAT'S HER STORY?

06:12.083 --> 06:15.041
SHE'S JUST GOT THE JITTERS.
IT'LL BE TEN MINUTES TOPS.

06:15.083 --> 06:18.542
SO, UH, PETE ASKED ME OUT.
DO I GO? NO, I MEAN, DO I GO,

06:18.583 --> 06:22.041
WITH THE DRY,
UNTOUCHED LIPS AND ALL?
I'M MAKING HUMAN LIFE HERE.

06:22.083 --> 06:25.041
PATIENT.
I WILL SEE HER NOW.

06:25.083 --> 06:27.959
(singsong voice) THANK YOU.

06:28.000 --> 06:31.583
HI.

06:31.625 --> 06:36.667
YOU... ASKED ME OUT,
AND THEN YOU BLEW ME OFF. HI.

06:36.709 --> 06:38.041
I DIDN'T BLOW YOU OFF.

06:38.083 --> 06:40.625
I HAD TRAINING
FOR THE S.W.A.T. TEAM.

06:40.667 --> 06:43.041
I'M S.W.A.T. NOW.

06:43.083 --> 06:45.709
YOU SHOW THAT
TO ALL THE GIRLS?
NO, JUST THE CUTE ONES.

06:45.750 --> 06:48.500
MM.
BUT I'M HERE NOW.
I'M AVAILABLE.

06:48.542 --> 06:50.041
I HAVE A PATIENT.

06:50.083 --> 06:52.041
AND YOU ARE JUST A STRANGER,

06:52.083 --> 06:56.041
SOME GUY I MET, YOU KNOW,
AND I DON'T GET BLOWN OFF.

06:56.083 --> 06:58.500
I AM NOT THE KIND OF WOMAN
YOU BLOW OFF.

06:58.542 --> 07:00.667
YOU HAVE YOUR PRIDE.
I HAVE MY PRIDE, YES.

07:00.709 --> 07:03.667
GO AWAY.
GO S.W.A.T. SOMETHING.

07:05.083 --> 07:09.125
MOLLY, ERIC.
HI, I'M DR. MONTGOMERY.

07:09.166 --> 07:11.625
WHERE'S DR. BENNETT?
SHE HAS ANOTHER PATIENT.

07:11.667 --> 07:14.041
WE NEED TO SEE DR. BENNETT.

07:14.083 --> 07:16.041
WELL, WHY DON'T WE JUST SEE

07:16.083 --> 07:18.250
IF I CAN FIND OUT
WHAT THE PROBLEM IS FIRST?

07:18.291 --> 07:20.542
LET'S SEE--
27 WEEKS PREGNANT,

07:20.583 --> 07:22.542
ULTRASOUND FROM TWO DAYS AGO
LOOKS GOOD,

07:22.583 --> 07:25.041
OH, IT'S A GIRL,

07:25.083 --> 07:28.667
AND... PLACENTA POSITIONING
LOOKS GOOD.

07:28.709 --> 07:30.125
SO WHAT'S THE CONCERN?

07:30.166 --> 07:32.875
I-I NEED TO HAVE THIS BABY.
WELL, EVERYTHING'S ON TRACK.

07:32.917 --> 07:34.875
NO, THAT--
THAT'S NOT WHAT--ERIC.

07:34.917 --> 07:37.166
WE NEED TO HAVE
THIS BABY NOW.
TODAY IF POSSIBLE.

07:37.208 --> 07:39.166
I'M--I'M SORRY.
I'M NOT UNDERSTANDING.

07:39.208 --> 07:41.250
YOU'RE ONLY
SIX MONTHS PREGNANT.

07:41.291 --> 07:43.917
WELL, YOU HAVE TO INDUCE
OR DO A C-SECTION

07:43.959 --> 07:46.542
SO THAT I CAN
HAVE THIS BABY TODAY.

07:46.583 --> 07:49.041
IT HAS TO BE BORN.
PLEASE JUST--

07:49.083 --> 07:54.041
HE'LL DIE IF YOU DON'T.
HE--HE IS DYING, DAMN IT.

07:54.083 --> 07:56.291
I'M SORRY, WHO IS DYING?

07:56.333 --> 07:59.250
(sobs)
OUR SON JASON. HE'S 7.

07:59.291 --> 08:01.250
HE HAS
ACUTE LYMPHOBLASTIC LEUKEMIA.

08:01.291 --> 08:05.125
THE BABY'S CORD BLOOD'S THE ONLY
THING THAT CAN SAVE HIM.

08:12.750 --> 08:14.917
YOU'RE AVOIDING ME.

08:14.959 --> 08:17.917
I AM NOT AVOIDING YOU.
I'VE JUST BEEN BUSY--

08:17.959 --> 08:19.917
RUNNING THE PRACTICE
AND RAISING OUR DAUGHTER.

08:19.959 --> 08:22.041
ALWAYS KEEPING THE TRAINS
RUNNING ON TIME.

08:22.083 --> 08:24.166
TRAINS OR NO TRAINS,
WE WILL TALK.

08:27.750 --> 08:30.083
HEY, DO YOU HAVE A MINUTE?
NO, ACT--

08:30.125 --> 08:32.542
NO, SHE DOES NOT.

08:35.750 --> 08:39.041
WHAT?
MOLLY AND ERIC MADISON.

08:39.083 --> 08:41.542
YOU SELECTED THE EMBRYO THAT
MATCHED THEIR DYING SON...

08:41.583 --> 08:44.041
AND IMPLANTED IT.
SELECTIVE I.V.F.

08:44.083 --> 08:46.959
YOU CHOSE A GENETIC MATCH
FOR THEIR DYING SON

08:47.000 --> 08:48.250
AND IMPREGNATED HER?

08:48.291 --> 08:51.041
YES. I-I DO NOT UNDERSTAND
WHAT THE PROBLEM IS HERE?

08:51.083 --> 08:53.041
THE PROBLEM IS THAT
SHE'S CARRYING A CHILD,

08:53.083 --> 08:56.583
EXCEPT TO HER IT'S NOT A CHILD,
IT'S AN ORGAN DONOR.

08:56.625 --> 08:58.583
TO HER, SHE'S GROWING ORGANS
FOR HER SICK SON.

08:58.625 --> 09:00.959
NOT ORGANS.
THE UMBILICAL CORD BLOOD

09:01.000 --> 09:03.125
IS GOING TO BE COLLECTED
AT BIRTH, PROCESSED,

09:03.166 --> 09:08.041
AND THEN INFUSED INTO HER SON
TO SAVE HIS LIFE.
SAME THING, NAI.
MORALLY, ETHICALLY--

09:08.083 --> 09:10.667
IT'S A GRAY AREA TO GROW
A CHILD'S GENETIC MATCH.

09:10.709 --> 09:12.667
THIS IS DONE ALL THE TIME
AS A BACKUP.

09:12.709 --> 09:15.041
BUT HE IS DYING NOW,
AND SHE WANTS HER DAUGHTER

09:15.083 --> 09:16.667
DELIVERED
THREE MONTHS PREMATURE

09:16.709 --> 09:18.709
WITH NO REGARD
FOR THE BABY'S HEALTH.

09:20.333 --> 09:23.709
OH, GOD. I DIDN'T...

09:23.750 --> 09:27.041
THEY--THEY HAD
A PARTIAL MATCH DONOR.

09:27.083 --> 09:31.000
THE PARTIAL MATCH
HAS PNEUMONIA.

09:31.041 --> 09:32.500
ADDISON...

09:32.542 --> 09:34.667
THAT MEANS...

09:34.709 --> 09:36.875
THEIR SON HAS HAD
HIS IMMUNE SYSTEM STRIPPED

09:36.917 --> 09:38.917
IN PREPARATION FOR THE DONOR.

09:38.959 --> 09:41.625
HE'S IN THE HOSPITAL RIGHT NOW,
AND IF HE DOESN'T RECEIVE

09:41.667 --> 09:43.917
THAT CORD BLOOD
WITHIN THE WEEK, HE DIES.

09:43.959 --> 09:47.208
WELL, WHAT DID YOU TELL 'EM
ABOUT DELIVERING THE BABY?
I SAID NO.

09:47.250 --> 09:49.250
WHY?

09:49.291 --> 09:51.250
THANK YOU FOR THE UPDATE,
DR. KING.

09:51.291 --> 09:52.875
(elevator bell dings)

09:52.917 --> 09:54.709
YOU'RE WELCOME,
DR. FREEDMAN.

09:56.750 --> 09:58.709
HEY. I WAS JUST COMING--

09:58.750 --> 10:01.041
SO ON MNEMBA ISLAND,
THERE'S NO PHONES,

10:01.083 --> 10:03.542
THERE'S NO COMPUTER,
THERE'S NO TELEVISION.

10:03.583 --> 10:05.917
OUR BONUS CHECKS WILL BE PUT
TO VERY GOOD USE.

10:05.959 --> 10:07.917
UM, I DON'T KNOW. MAYBE.

10:07.959 --> 10:09.917
WE CAN TOUCH MONKEYS, COOPER.
WE CAN TOUCH MONKEYS.

10:09.959 --> 10:11.875
YEAH, OKAY. YOU MADE THAT
LAST PART UP. I HAVE PATIENTS.

10:11.917 --> 10:14.875
WELL, I HAVE PATIENTS, TOO,
AND AS I AM SEEING THEM,

10:14.917 --> 10:18.250
PART OF ME WILL BE CONJURING
IMAGES OF TOUCHABLE MONKEYS.

10:18.291 --> 10:20.667
DEAN.

10:20.709 --> 10:22.041
HEY, DR. FREEDMAN.

10:22.083 --> 10:23.709
HOW YOU BEEN?
GOOD.

10:23.750 --> 10:25.959
HOW ABOUT YOU?
HOW YOU BEEN?
IT WAS A GOOD MONTH.

10:26.000 --> 10:28.000
THAT'S WHAT I LIKE TO HEAR.

10:30.083 --> 10:32.709
DELL, THE NEW PATIENT
GOWNS BLOW. THEY KEEP RIPPING.

10:32.750 --> 10:35.041
YEAH, WE'RE WORKING OUT
THE KINKS WITH SOME NEW VENDORS.
WHAT'S WRONG
WITH THE OLD VENDORS?

10:35.083 --> 10:37.917
AND WHERE ARE THE--
DISHWASHER.

10:37.959 --> 10:39.750
(Cooper) YEAH,
EVERYTHING LOOKS GOOD.

10:39.792 --> 10:41.125
EVERYTHING AT SCHOOL GOOD?

10:41.166 --> 10:44.041
GOOD. I HAVE A GIRLFRIEND.
AMY. SHE'S AMAZING.

10:44.083 --> 10:46.041
WELL, GOOD.
YOU TAKING IT SLOW?

10:46.083 --> 10:49.709
WE HAVEN'T DONE IT... YET,
BUT SHE'S GOING ON THE PILL,

10:49.750 --> 10:52.667
SO WE WILL SOON.
BELIEVE ME WHEN I SAY

10:52.709 --> 10:54.875
I WILL NOT BE
THE FIRST OF MY FRIENDS.

10:54.917 --> 10:57.208
OH, I KNOW, BUT, UM,
CONDOMS, OKAY?
(sighs)

10:57.250 --> 10:59.208
HEY, S.T.D.s DON'T CARE
ABOUT THE PILL.

10:59.250 --> 11:01.625
CONDOMS ARE YOUR FRIEND--
LOTS OF CONDOMS.

11:01.667 --> 11:03.625
OR BETTER YET, YOU KNOW,
WAIT.

11:03.667 --> 11:06.917
IF THIS IS THE GIRL, YOU OUGHT
TO ENJOY THE TIME BEFORE,

11:06.959 --> 11:08.917
BECAUSE ONCE YOU'RE ON
THE OTHER SIDE,

11:08.959 --> 11:10.792
YOU CAN'T GO BACK.
HELLO.

11:10.834 --> 11:13.041
YOU JUST HEARD "BLAH, BLAH,
BLAH, BLAH, BLAH, BLAH, BLAH"?

11:13.083 --> 11:15.041
DR. FREEDMAN,
I'M GONNA HAVE SEX,

11:15.083 --> 11:17.000
AND I REALLY LIKE HER.

11:17.041 --> 11:19.000
IT'S NOT ALL SKANKY.
IT'S RIGHT.

11:19.041 --> 11:22.083
I, LIKE, LOVE HER
AND EVERYTHING.

11:22.125 --> 11:23.709
(mouths word)

11:23.750 --> 11:26.709
WELL... NOW I GO BACK
TO MY CONDOM SPEECH.

11:26.750 --> 11:29.041
SO I AM YOUR FRIENDLY

11:29.083 --> 11:31.875
NEIGHBORHOOD
CONDOM PUSHER MAN.

