CONDOMS.

11:34.917 --> 11:37.834
IF YOU CAN SAVE THEIR SON BY
DELIVERING THE BABY, I DON'T--

11:37.875 --> 11:40.834
6-MONTH PREEMIES ARE AT RISK
FOR BRAIN BLEEDS, BLINDNESS,

11:40.875 --> 11:42.875
HEARING LOSS, NOT TO MENTION
RESPIRATORY DISTRESS.

11:42.917 --> 11:45.250
AND NO ONE WOULD ADVOCATE
BRINGING A CHILD

11:45.291 --> 11:47.875
INTO THE WORLD BEFORE
SHE'S READY, AND YOU KNOW IT.

11:47.917 --> 11:50.542
DID YOU EVEN CONSIDER THE FACT
THAT THIS LITTLE GIRL

11:50.583 --> 11:52.625
IS ARRIVING INTO A FAMILY
UNWANTED?

11:52.667 --> 11:54.875
WHAT HAPPENS WHEN SHE DISCOVERS
THAT THE ONLY REASON

11:54.917 --> 11:57.250
SHE WAS CONCEIVED
WAS TO SAVE HER BROTHER'S LIFE?
WE ARE TALKING ABOUT

11:57.291 --> 12:00.041
SAVING THIS FAMILY FROM
SUFFERING THE DEATH OF A CHILD.

12:00.083 --> 12:03.709
YOU GAVE THEM HOPE
THEY SHOULDN'T HAVE. I--
I'M TRYING TO SAVE
A CHILD'S LIFE.

12:03.750 --> 12:05.583
YOU DISCUSS THIS STUFF
WITH US.

12:05.625 --> 12:08.208
WHEN ANY OF US COME INTO
AN ETHICAL GRAY AREA,

12:08.250 --> 12:10.208
WE ALL DISCUSS IT.

12:10.250 --> 12:12.208
WE DECIDE AS A PRACTICE
WHAT TO DO.

12:12.250 --> 12:14.917
I MEANT TO, ALL RIGHT?
I... I JUST FORGOT.

12:14.959 --> 12:18.208
SINCE WHEN DO YOU
FORGET ANYTHING?

12:18.250 --> 12:20.208
IF I COULD GET ONE GUY

12:20.250 --> 12:22.500
TO DO A COLONOSCOPY
WITH NO COMPLAINT...

12:22.542 --> 12:25.500
I MEAN, LIKE I'M HAPPY ABOUT
GOING ALL UP IN THERE.

12:25.542 --> 12:27.041
WHAT ARE YOU LOOKING FOR?

12:27.083 --> 12:29.041
I'M TRYING
TO LEAVE YOU A NOTE,

12:29.083 --> 12:31.500
BUT I CAN'T FIND A PEN
THAT WORKS.
WELL, WHAT'S--WHAT'S THE NOTE?

12:31.542 --> 12:34.041
HOW I CAN'T FIND A PEN
THAT WORKS.

12:34.083 --> 12:36.041
DELL HAS DECIDED TO GO GREEN--
TISSUE PAPER GOWNS,

12:36.083 --> 12:38.083
NO CUPS, NO PENS.

12:38.125 --> 12:41.625
I'M ALL ABOUT SAVING THE PLANET,
BUT HE'S KILLING ME.
YOU WANT ME TO TALK TO DELL?

12:41.667 --> 12:43.625
WE BOTH KNOW
WHO DELL LISTENS TO.

12:43.667 --> 12:44.959
IS THIS NAOMI'S IDEA?

12:45.000 --> 12:47.750
I HAVE NO CLUE
WHAT NAOMI'S IDEAS ARE.

12:47.792 --> 12:51.041
MY WOMAN'S GIVING ME TROUBLE.
YOUR WOMAN'S GIVING YOU TROUBLE.

12:51.083 --> 12:53.041
THESE WOMEN, COOPER.

12:53.083 --> 12:55.125
WHAT?

12:55.166 --> 12:58.542
14-YEAR-OLD KID, I'VE BEEN
TREATING HIM SINCE HE WAS 5.

12:58.583 --> 13:01.041
NOW HE'S FOUND THIS GIRL--
HE LIKES HER,

13:01.083 --> 13:03.041
THEY'RE GONNA HAVE SEX.
THAT'S HARDLY A SHOCKER.

13:03.083 --> 13:06.041
WAIT, DON'T TELL ME
YOU'RE GETTING ALL NOSTALGIC.
IT'S DEAN MILLER.

13:06.083 --> 13:08.542
OH, MAN.
WHY DOES
THAT NAME SOUND FAMILIAR?

13:08.583 --> 13:11.000
BECAUSE WE DEBATED WHETHER
WE SHOULD TAKE HIM ON

13:11.041 --> 13:13.583
AS A PATIENT.
HE'S THE KID WHO--

13:13.625 --> 13:16.125
HE'S H.I.V. POSITIVE,
BUT THAT WASN'T THE DEBATE.
THE PROBLEM IS, HE DOESN'T
KNOW HE'S H.I.V. POSITIVE.

13:16.166 --> 13:18.709
HIS PARENTS WON'T TELL HIM,

13:18.750 --> 13:21.041
AND HE DOESN'T KNOW
HE COULD KILL THAT GIRL.

13:25.500 --> 13:27.709
HE THINKS
HE HAS A KIDNEY CONDITION,

13:27.750 --> 13:30.000
AND HE'S DOING QUITE WELL.
I MEAN, THE MAJORITY

13:30.041 --> 13:32.667
OF HIS SYMPTOMS ARE FROM
THE ANTIVIRAL COCKTAIL.
HOW DO YOU
KEEP SOMETHING LIKE THAT

13:32.709 --> 13:35.000
FROM YOUR KID FOR 14 YEARS?
IT WAS BEFORE
THE PROGNOSIS CHANGED.

13:35.041 --> 13:36.959
THEY DIDN'T THINK
HE WAS GONNA BE ALIVE

13:37.000 --> 13:39.583
LONG ENOUGH TO UNDERSTAND.
SO THAT EXPLAINS
THE FIRST SIX YEARS.

13:39.625 --> 13:41.583
I'M NOT ALLOWED TO TELL HIM
ABOUT THE H.I.V.

13:41.625 --> 13:43.625
I'M NOT ALLOWED
TO TELL THE PARENTS

13:43.667 --> 13:45.083
ANYTHING THAT DEAN TELLS ME.

13:45.125 --> 13:46.583
DOCTOR-PATIENT CONFIDENTIALITY
ALL AROUND.
SO YOU CAN'T

13:46.625 --> 13:49.291
LET 'EM KNOW
ABOUT THE GIRLFRIEND.
NO, OR THAT
THEY'RE GONNA DO IT.

13:49.333 --> 13:52.208
THIS IS A GOOD KID.
HE WOULD NOT ENDANGER THIS GIRL

13:52.250 --> 13:54.208
IF HE KNEW, AND HE DOESN'T.

13:54.250 --> 13:56.917
HIS HORMONES ARE FULL ROAR,
RIGHT? HE LIKES THE GIRL.

13:56.959 --> 13:59.083
HE WANTS THE GIRL.
HE'S GOTTA HAVE THE GIRL.
(Sam) WE'VE ALL BEEN THERE.

13:59.125 --> 14:01.041
YES, WE HAVE.

14:01.083 --> 14:02.542
ANYWAY...

14:02.583 --> 14:04.041
YOU KNOW WHAT?

14:04.083 --> 14:07.000
I GOTTA TRY TO GET
HIS PARENTS BACK IN MY OFFICE.

14:09.083 --> 14:10.917
(Molly) HE LOVES BUGS.

14:10.959 --> 14:14.959
AND HE SNEAKS LADYBUGS
INTO THE HOUSE IN HIS POCKET.

14:15.000 --> 14:17.792
HE LIKES MEATBALLS...
(chuckles) AND FRENCH FRIES.

14:17.834 --> 14:20.625
(sniffles) AND HE'S STILL
AFRAID OF THE DARK,

14:20.667 --> 14:23.041
BUT HE THINKS
HE'S TOO OLD TO ADMIT IT,

14:23.083 --> 14:24.667
SO I HAVE TO PRETEND

14:24.709 --> 14:26.875
TO FORGET TO TURN OFF
THE LIGHT AT BEDTIME.

14:26.917 --> 14:29.875
AND HE LIKES TO READ. AND ALL
HE WANTS FOR HIS 8th BIRTHDAY

14:29.917 --> 14:32.542
IS TO NEVER GO
TO A HOSPITAL AGAIN.

14:32.583 --> 14:35.041
HE--HE'S A WONDERFUL BOY.

14:35.083 --> 14:38.834
I CAN SEE THAT,
BUT, MRS. MADISON, I CAN'T.

14:38.875 --> 14:41.834
IN GOOD CONSCIENCE, I CAN'T
DELIVER YOUR BABY EARLY

14:41.875 --> 14:43.959
BECAUSE I'M SURE
SHE'S WONDERFUL, TOO.

14:44.000 --> 14:46.875
WE ARE GOOD PEOPLE AND--AND WE
DIDN'T GO INTO THIS LIGHTLY--

14:46.917 --> 14:48.875
HAVING THIS BABY--
AND WE WILL LOVE HER.

14:48.917 --> 14:51.250
WE WILL. IT'S JUST,
WE DON'T KNOW HER YET.

14:51.291 --> 14:55.041
AND... I-I KNOW JASON.

14:55.083 --> 14:57.917
I'VE HELD JASON.
I--I'VE SMELLED HIS SKIN.

14:57.959 --> 14:59.583
I-I KNOW JASON.

14:59.625 --> 15:00.959
I'M SO SORRY.

15:01.000 --> 15:04.625
I--I'VE CHECKED YOU OUT.
YOU'RE A SPECIALIST.

15:04.667 --> 15:08.083
IF--IF ANYONE CAN DELIVER
A PREMATURE BABY SAFELY,

15:08.125 --> 15:09.917
IT'S YOU.

15:13.625 --> 15:16.583
I WISH I COULD HELP,
BUT THERE'S NOTHING I CAN DO.

15:16.625 --> 15:18.583
HOW CAN YOU
LOOK AT MY 7-YEAR-OLD SON

15:18.625 --> 15:23.000
AND KNOW HE'S GOING TO BE DEAD
IN A WEEK AND DO NOTHING?
(whispers) PLEASE.

15:30.583 --> 15:32.041
(elevator bell dings)
ADDISON--

15:32.083 --> 15:34.125
DON'T TALK TO ME.
ADDI--

15:34.166 --> 15:37.125
DON'T SAY ANYTHING, PLEASE.
JUST DON'T.
ADDISON, I WAS NOT TRYING
TO MANIPULATE YOU.

15:37.166 --> 15:40.041
I JUST THOUGHT IF YOU SAW HIM,
MAYBE YOU WOULD REALIZE

15:40.083 --> 15:42.041
THAT YOU CAN HELP THEM.
I CAN'T HELP THEM!

15:42.083 --> 15:44.041
YOU GAVE THEM HOPE
THEY SHOULDN'T HAVE,

15:44.083 --> 15:48.041
AND NOW I AM THE BAD GUY.
ADDISON.

15:48.083 --> 15:50.500
I TOLD YOU
NOT TO SAY ANYTHING TO ME.

15:53.250 --> 15:56.000
HEY, I REALLY DO
NEED TO TALK TO YOU.
NOT NOW, DELL.

15:59.125 --> 16:01.917
(sighs)

16:01.959 --> 16:03.917
ARE YOU OKAY?
(Sam) WHAT'S GOING ON?

16:03.959 --> 16:05.792
(Pete)
HAS THERE BEEN BLOODSHED?

16:05.834 --> 16:08.583
BECAUSE NAOMI IS IN THE KITCHEN
JUST INHALING THE CANDY SUPPLY.

16:08.625 --> 16:11.917
COME ON. IT WAS LOW
TO BEGIN WITH.
WELL, DELL REFUSES TO BUY
ANY NEW CANDY.

16:11.959 --> 16:14.041
WAIT, HE'S WITHHOLDING CANDY?
HE TOLD ME TO "MAKE DUE"

16:14.083 --> 16:17.041
WITH THE SWEET TARTS
FROM LAST HALLOWEEN?
WELL, NOBODY CAN HANDLE
THE OLD SWEET TARTS.

16:17.083 --> 16:20.083
WE NEED CHOCOLATE.
NO, I TOLD--I TOLD DELL
THAT HE HAD TO GET--

16:20.125 --> 16:22.250
THIS HAS NOTHING TO DO
WITH CANDY.

16:22.291 --> 16:24.041
(sighs)

16:24.083 --> 16:26.250
I CAN'T DO ANYTHING.
I CAN'T SAVE THAT CHILD.

16:26.291 --> 16:27.875
I CAN'T DELIVER THE BABY.

16:27.917 --> 16:31.041
TO THE BEST
OF MY MEDICAL EXPERTISE...

16:31.083 --> 16:34.208
I CANNOT DO... ANYTHING.

16:34.250 --> 16:36.083
DON'T BEAT YOURSELF UP.

16:36.125 --> 16:38.291
IT'S NOT YOUR MESS.
IT'S NAOMI'S.
WAIT, YOU MEAN THE MADISONS?

16:38.333 --> 16:40.834
BECAUSE NAOMI DID
WHAT SHE THOUGHT WAS RIGHT.

16:40.875 --> 16:43.041
YOU DO WHAT YOU NEED TO DO
TO SAVE YOUR FAMILY.

16:43.083 --> 16:45.542
SHE HAD NO WAY OF KNOWING
THE DONOR WOULD BACK OUT,

16:45.583 --> 16:47.917
AND NOW IT'S TOO LATE.
BUT WE ALWAYS DISCUSS
THESE THINGS AS A GROUP.

16:47.959 --> 16:50.166
NAOMI WENT AHEAD AND DID THIS
WITHOUT TALKING TO ANYBODY.

16:50.208 --> 16:52.291
SO MAYBE
SHE'S OFF HER GAME.

16:52.333 --> 16:54.917
SHE'S SEEING A RECORD NUMBER
OF PATIENTS A DAY--
SHE'S BEEN
REALLY ON EDGE LATELY.

16:54.959 --> 16:57.542
YEAH, IT'S NOT LIKE HER.
WELL, GUYS, I MEAN,

16:57.583 --> 16:58.917
SHE DOES EVERYTHING.

16:58.959 --> 17:01.000
WE JUST...
EAT THE CANDY.

17:01.041 --> 17:02.583
SHE'S HIDING SOMETHING.

17:02.625 --> 17:04.792
HAS ANYBODY EVEN ASKED HER
WHAT'S WRONG?

17:04.834 --> 17:07.166
(Cooper)
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

17:07.208 --> 17:09.500
THIS I CAN
DO SOMETHING ABOUT.

17:12.041 --> 17:14.667
WHO'D WIN IN A FISTFIGHT,
NAOMI OR ADDISON?

17:17.625 --> 17:19.875
NOT IN THE MOOD
FOR A LECTURE.

17:19.917 --> 17:22.875
OH, I'M NOT GONNA LECTURE YOU.
I'M JUST GONNA BLOCK THE EXITS

17:22.917 --> 17:26.250
UNTIL YOU DECIDE TO TELL ME
WHAT'S GOING ON WITH YOU.
WELL, WE'RE GONNA BE HERE
A VERY LONG TIME.

17:26.291 --> 17:28.083
I CAN WAIT.
(clears throat)

17:35.083 --> 17:37.625
(Cooper) WHAT, THEY'RE NOT
EVEN SAYING ANYTHING?

17:37.667 --> 17:39.625
THEY'RE JUST
STANDING THERE.
A TEST OF WILLS.

17:39.667 --> 17:41.208
A BATTLE OF CHAMPIONS.
UH-HUH.

17:41.250 --> 17:44.083
YOU GUYS ARE SO MATURE.
OH, YEAH? YOU MENTIONED
A FISTFIGHT.

17:44.125 --> 17:45.625
THAT'S TRUE.

17:45.667 --> 17:48.041
COOPER.

17:48.083 --> 17:49.667
DEAN'S PARENTS ARE HERE...

17:49.709 --> 17:50.875
THANKS.

17:50.917 --> 17:52.500
AND EVERYONE ELSE.

17:52.542 --> 17:54.875
THERE'S A LOBBY
FULL OF PATIENTS...
(clears throat)

17:54.917 --> 17:57.500
IN CASE ANYONE IS INTERESTED
IN WORKING HERE

17:57.542 --> 17:59.500
OR RUNNING THIS PLACE.

17:59.542 --> 18:02.500
THERE'S A GIRL DEAN LIKES,
BUT SEX IS A LONG WAY OFF.

18:02.542 --> 18:04.500
I'VE HAD PREGNANT
13 YEAR OLDS

18:04.542 --> 18:06.500
WHOSE PARENTS
HAVE SAID THE SAME THING.

18:06.542 --> 18:08.917
DEAN NEEDS TO KNOW
HIS H.I.V. STATUS

18:08.959 --> 18:11.291
BEFORE HE STARTS EXPERIMENTING.
AND HE WILL.

18:11.333 --> 18:13.291
WHAT I'M SAYING IS,
YOU CAN'T AFFORD TO WAIT.

18:13.333 --> 18:16.625
YOU HAVE ANY IDEA WHAT IT'S
LIKE FOR H.I.V. KIDS?

18:16.667 --> 18:18.667
A KID IN CHICAGO GOT SHOT.

18:18.709 --> 18:21.041
ANOTHER KID, THEY TIED HIM
TO A CAR BUMPER.
THAT'S BEFORE PEOPLE
WERE EDUCATED.

18:21.083 --> 18:23.709
NOBODY NEEDS TO KNOW
BUT DEAN.
HE'S NOT OLD ENOUGH
TO DEAL WITH THIS, NOT YET.

18:23.750 --> 18:26.667
YOU WANT THEM TO BE CHILDREN
AS LONG AS IT LASTS.

18:26.709 --> 18:28.667
THINGS ARE SO SWEET,
THEY CAN STILL BE ANYTHING.

18:28.709 --> 18:30.083
AS SOON AS THAT'S OVER--

18:30.125 --> 18:32.542
I WISH IT COULD BE LONGER,
BUT IT CAN'T.

18:32.583 --> 18:34.917
YOU SAY PEOPLE ARE EDUCATED?
THEY'LL UNDERSTAND?

18:34.959 --> 18:37.625
IF IT WAS YOUR KID,
YOU WOULDN'T BE SO SURE.

18:37.667 --> 18:39.875
COULD YOU HONESTLY LIVE
WITH YOURSELVES--
DO YOU NOT HEAR ME?

18:39.917 --> 18:41.959
IF HE GETS ANOTHER KID SICK,
WHAT HAPPENS WHEN HE FINDS OUT

18:42.000 --> 18:45.166
THAT YOU DIDN'T--
WE WILL DO WHAT'S BEST FOR HIM,
AND DON'T YOU OVERSTEP HERE.

18:45.208 --> 18:47.166
YOU'RE NOT LEAVING ME
MUCH CHOICE.

18:47.208 --> 18:50.166
SAY ONE WORD TO DEAN,
AND I--I'LL TAKE YOUR LICENSE.

18:50.208 --> 18:53.542
I WILL SUE YOU
FOR EVERYTHING YOU'VE GOT.

18:59.625 --> 19:02.125
NAI... COME ON.
YOU CAN TELL ME ANYTHING.

19:02.166 --> 19:04.750
IT'S NOT LIKE YOU TO GET
THE MADISONS PREGNANT

19:04.792 --> 19:07.125
WITHOUT DISCUSSING IT
WITH THE REST OF US.

19:07.166 --> 19:09.875
NOW I KNOW YOU MUST HAVE
HAD A GOOD REASON.

19:09.917 --> 19:13.166
YOU HAVE A GOOD HEART.
JUST TALK TO ME.

19:15.083 --> 19:17.041
THEY PAID THE PRACTICE
$80,000.

19:17.083 --> 19:20.125
AND I DON'T HAVE
A GOOD HEART.

19:20.166 --> 19:22.750
THEY HAD CASH,
AND WE NEEDED THE MONEY,

19:22.792 --> 19:24.625
AND SO I TOOK IT

19:24.667 --> 19:26.625
EVEN THOUGH
I DID HAVE RESERVATIONS,

19:26.667 --> 19:29.750
BECAUSE NAOMI ALWAYS KEEPS
THE TRAINS RUNNING ON TIME.

19:29.792 --> 19:32.542
WHAT, UH, WHAT DO YOU--
WHAT DO YOU MEAN? WHAT--

19:32.583 --> 19:35.291
I KEEP THE TRAINS RUNNING
ON TIME. THAT'S WHAT I DO.

19:35.333 --> 19:37.291
I RUN THINGS.
I MIND THE DETAILS.

19:37.333 --> 19:40.709
ONLY THIS TIME, IT...
JUST GOT AWAY FROM ME.

19:40.750 --> 19:43.041
WHAT GOT AWAY FROM YOU?

19:43.083 --> 19:45.583
(lowered voice)
YOU CAN'T TELL ANYBODY.

19:45.625 --> 19:48.583
YOU CANNOT TELL THE OTHERS.
YOU HAVE TO PROMISE.
WHAT, UM, OKAY, I PROMISE.

19:48.625 --> 19:51.083
WHAT, ARE YOU--YOU'RE TALKING
ABOUT THE PRACTICE?

19:51.125 --> 19:53.125
(normal voice)
WE OWN THE BUILDING.

19:53.166 --> 19:55.667
AND--AND I SAW A CHANCE
TO REFINANCE THE MORTGAGE,

19:55.709 --> 19:57.250
AND I THOUGHT...

19:57.291 --> 20:00.041
NOW THE BALLOON PAYMENT
IS DUE,

20:00.083 --> 20:03.625
AND NO ONE IS BILLING ENOUGH,
AND THERE ISN'T ENOUGH.

20:03.667 --> 20:06.041
THERE IS NEVER ENOUGH.
(sighs)

20:06.083 --> 20:09.041
AND SO I USED THE LAST OF
THE MONEY TO MAKE THE VIDEO.

20:09.083 --> 20:11.250
NAOMI--
WE ARE BROKE, ADDISON.

20:11.291 --> 20:14.208
IF THINGS KEEP GOING
THE WAY THEY HAVE BEEN,

20:14.250 --> 20:17.625
THE PRACTICE IS FINISHED...
SOON.

20:21.792 --> 20:23.041
ALL RIGHT, SCREW THEM.

20:23.083 --> 20:25.083
WE LET THEM COME AFTER ME.
THEY REALLY THINK

20:25.125 --> 20:27.583
A JURY'S GONNA BACK THEM
WHEN THEY'RE PERFECTLY HAPPY

20:27.625 --> 20:30.875
TO LET THEIR SON INFECT
SOME NICE GIRL FROM THE 'BURBS?
THE LAW SAYS THEY HAVE
THE RIGHT TO DO THIS

20:30.917 --> 20:33.083
HOW THEY WANT TO DO THIS.
I'M TAKING MY CHANCES.
I'M GONNA TELL DEAN.

20:33.125 --> 20:35.250
IF THEY SUE,
THEY SUE THE PRACTICE.

20:35.291 --> 20:38.208
WHY DON'T YOU THINK ABOUT
SOMEONE OTHER THAN YOURSELF?

20:38.250 --> 20:41.208
WHOA, NAOMI. COOP'S JUST TRYING
TO DO THE RIGHT THING, HERE.
HE'S TALKING ABOUT
GETTING US SUED.

20:41.250 --> 20:43.083
THERE ARE
RESPONSIBILITIES HERE.

20:43.125 --> 20:45.083
SO YOU THINK THAT FAMILY
HAS THE RIGHT

20:45.125 --> 20:47.250
TO HIDE IMPORTANT INFORMATION
FROM EACH OTHER?

20:47.291 --> 20:50.709
SOMETIMES PEOPLE HIDE THINGS
FOR GOOD REASON.
HIDING THINGS
IS NO WAY TO PROTECT THEM.

20:50.750 --> 20:53.041
IT IS WHEN YOU'RE
THE ONE IN CHARGE.
(Pete) WHOA. WHOA.

20:53.083 --> 20:55.667
EVERYBODY BREATHE.
(Sam) COOPER'S GONNA
FIGURE OUT A WAY.

20:55.709 --> 20:57.583
HE ALWAYS DOES.

20:57.625 --> 21:00.834
♪♪

21:04.667 --> 21:07.041
MM.

21:07.083 --> 21:08.709
HEY.

21:08.750 --> 21:10.125
IS IT WISE?
HUH?

21:10.166 --> 21:12.959
OUR DATE.
OH.

21:13.041 --> 21:15.041
UM, I HAVEN'T HAD TIME--

21:15.083 --> 21:18.667
CAN WE TALK
ABOUT THIS TOMORROW?

21:18.709 --> 21:22.709
♪♪

21:22.750 --> 21:25.542
SO YOU, UH, YOU READY
TO TALK YET?

21:25.583 --> 21:28.041
NO, I AM NOT READY
TO TALK...

21:28.083 --> 21:29.542
ABOUT ANYTHING.

21:29.583 --> 21:31.625
GOOD NIGHT, GUYS.
OKAY.

21:31.667 --> 21:33.041
WAIT, HEY--
GOOD NIGHT.

21:33.083 --> 21:34.583
(Cooper) GOOD NIGHT.

21:34.625 --> 21:36.125
THESE WOMEN.

21:36.166 --> 21:37.125
SHOTS.

21:37.166 --> 21:38.542
YEAH.

21:38.583 --> 21:40.583
(chuckles)

21:40.625 --> 21:42.083
♪♪

21:42.125 --> 21:44.083
COOPER ALWAYS
FIGURES OUT A WAY?

21:44.125 --> 21:46.792
COOPER DOES NOT ALWAYS
FIGURE OUT A WAY.

21:46.834 --> 21:49.166
YOU KNOW WHAT'S GONNA
MAKE YOU FEEL BETTER? MNEMBA.
MNEMBA.

21:49.208 --> 21:51.875
(laughs)
MONKEY TOUCHING.

21:51.917 --> 21:53.875
I GOT THE PAMPHLETS
RIGHT HERE.
VIOLET.

21:53.917 --> 21:55.875
THERE'S PRETTY GIRLS
IN THE PAMPHLETS,

21:55.917 --> 21:58.583
AND THEY MIGHT DO DIRTY,
TRASHY THINGS TO YOU

21:58.625 --> 22:00.583
WHEN I'M IN THE SPA.

22:00.625 --> 22:03.583
IS THAT WHAT THIS IS ABOUT?

22:03.625 --> 22:05.291
A GIRL? IS THERE...

22:05.333 --> 22:08.625
COOPER DO YOU HAVE A WOMAN
THAT I DON'T KNOW ABOUT,

22:08.667 --> 22:11.291
A NON-CYBER WOMAN?
THERE'S NO WOMAN.

22:11.333 --> 22:13.291
THEN WHAT IS IT?
IT'S BONUS TIME.

22:13.333 --> 22:15.917
WE ALWAYS BLOW HALF OF IT
ON SUNBURNS

22:15.959 --> 22:18.083
AND HAZY MEMORIES, COOP.

22:18.125 --> 22:20.208
VIOLET, DON'T COUNT ON ME
THIS YEAR.

22:20.250 --> 22:22.542
♪♪

22:25.041 --> 22:27.000
(laughs)

22:27.041 --> 22:28.834
MMM.

22:28.875 --> 22:31.041
WANT TO PLAY
NAUGHTY LITTLE SCHOOLBOY?

22:31.083 --> 22:32.291
MISTRESS AND BUTLER?

22:32.333 --> 22:36.041
I COULD BE THE WARDEN,
YOU COULD BE MY PRISONER.

22:36.083 --> 22:37.625
HOW ABOUT...

22:37.667 --> 22:39.625
BOYFRIEND AND GIRLFRIEND?

22:39.667 --> 22:41.000
(snorts)
DAMN IT, COOPER.

22:41.041 --> 22:43.041
OW. (coughs)

22:43.083 --> 22:45.041
YOU REALLY KNOW
HOW TO DRY A GIRL UP.

22:45.083 --> 22:47.041
OKAY, FIRST OF ALL,
IT WAS A SUGGESTION.

22:47.083 --> 22:49.041
AND SECOND OF ALL,
I LIED TODAY.

22:49.083 --> 22:51.875
I TOLD VIOLET A LIE. I TOLD HER
I WASN'T SEEING ANYBODY.

22:51.917 --> 22:53.875
WOULD YOU RATHER
LIE TO VIOLET

22:53.917 --> 22:55.875
AND PLAY NAUGHTY SCHOOLBOY
WITH ME,

22:55.917 --> 22:57.875
OR TELL HER THE TRUTH
AND PLAY WITH YOURSELF?

22:57.917 --> 23:00.625
(whispers) WHY DO WE
HAVE TO KEEP IT A SECRET?

23:00.667 --> 23:02.542
'CAUSE Y'ALL ARE ONE BIG
INCESTUOUS FAMILY,

23:02.583 --> 23:04.542
AND I'M NOT JOINING
THE FAMILY.

23:04.583 --> 23:06.834
THIS ISN'T THAT SERIOUS.

23:14.834 --> 23:16.583
I'M SICK
OF KEEPING SECRETS,

23:16.625 --> 23:19.583
AND I'M REALLY SICK OF KEEPING
SECRETS FROM MY BEST FRIEND.

23:19.625 --> 23:22.000
SO... MAYBE YOU SHOULD
JUST GO.

23:24.542 --> 23:26.083
(clears throat)

23:26.125 --> 23:29.250
I'M WEARING
CROTCHLESS PANTIES, COOP.

23:29.291 --> 23:31.250
(sighs)

23:31.291 --> 23:34.166
NO, NO. NO.
I AM NOT YOUR TOY.

23:34.208 --> 23:36.500
THERE'S A LOT OF OTHER THINGS
I COULD BE DOING,

23:36.542 --> 23:38.041
YOU KNOW, BETTER THINGS.

23:38.083 --> 23:41.041
I COULD BE TRAVELING. I COULD BE
TOUCHING MONKEYS IN MNEMBA.
MNEMBA?

23:41.083 --> 23:43.041
ZANZIBAR.
AND YOU COULD BE WITH ME

23:43.083 --> 23:45.041
IF YOU WEREN'T
PATHOLOGICALLY ALLERGIC

23:45.083 --> 23:47.917
TO HUMAN RELATIONSHIPS.

23:53.792 --> 23:55.125
(door closes)

23:55.166 --> 23:57.250
(groans)

23:57.291 --> 24:00.125
CROTCHLESS PANTIES.

24:01.875 --> 24:04.125
(sighs)

24:09.083 --> 24:10.250
(sighs)

24:10.291 --> 24:11.667
HEY.

24:11.709 --> 24:12.917
HEY.

24:15.583 --> 24:17.959
DID NAOMI SAY ANYTHING
TO YOU?

24:18.000 --> 24:20.917
WHAT...
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

24:20.959 --> 24:23.542
IN THE KITCHEN, DID SHE
TELL YOU WHAT WAS WRONG?

24:23.583 --> 24:27.041
OH, NO. I-I THINK
SHE'S JUST TIRED.
I THINK IT'S ME.

24:27.083 --> 24:29.667
I'VE BEEN PRESSURING HER
TO TALK ABOUT US.

24:29.709 --> 24:31.667
I JUST WANTED A SECOND CHANCE,

24:31.709 --> 24:34.667
AND I DON'T THINK
SHE WANTS TO GIVE IT TO ME.

24:34.709 --> 24:38.041
I THINK THIS IS HER WAY
OF TELLING ME THAT...

24:38.083 --> 24:40.875
IT'S OVER BETWEEN US.

24:40.917 --> 24:43.000
NO, SAM. I'M SURE
THAT'S NOT WHAT IT IS.

24:43.041 --> 24:45.041
THEN WHAT IS IT?

24:45.083 --> 24:47.041
IT'S LIKE I SAID.
SHE'S JUST... TIRED.

24:47.083 --> 24:48.959
ALL RIGHT.

25:13.333 --> 25:15.542
(elevator bell dings)

25:15.583 --> 25:17.542
(indistinct conversations)

25:17.583 --> 25:21.041
YEAH, YEAH,
THAT'S FINE. ALL RIGHT.

25:21.083 --> 25:22.834
ADDISON...

25:22.875 --> 25:25.709
HE HAS NO IDEA
WHAT IS GOING ON WITH YOU.

25:25.750 --> 25:27.959
IF YOU--
NO. NO.

25:28.000 --> 25:30.041
(two cell phones ring)

25:30.083 --> 25:32.500
THIS IS DR. MONTGOMERY.
THIS IS DR. BENNETT.

25:35.709 --> 25:38.250
WE'LL BE RIGHT THERE.
I'LL DRIVE.
I'LL CALL CHARLOTTE KING

25:38.291 --> 25:41.041
TO GET YOU SURGICAL PRIVILEGES
AT THE HOSPITAL.

25:41.083 --> 25:43.125
DELL, CANCEL MY PATIENTS
FOR THE REST OF THE DAY.

25:43.166 --> 25:45.041
YOU SAID
THIS WAS AN EMERGENCY.

25:45.083 --> 25:47.667
I THOUGHT THAT MEANT THERE WAS
SOMETHING IN HIS LABS.

25:47.709 --> 25:49.667
NO, HE'S FINE.

25:49.709 --> 25:51.834
DEAN... YOUR MOM AND DAD,

25:51.875 --> 25:54.667
THEY STILL THINK OF YOU
AS BEING A KID.

25:54.709 --> 25:56.792
WELL, I AM...
MOSTLY A KID.

25:56.834 --> 25:59.625
YEAH, BUT YOU'RE NOT A KID.
THAT'S NOT WHAT I SEE.

25:59.667 --> 26:01.625
THAT'S NOT WHAT I HEAR
FROM YOU.

26:03.709 --> 26:06.041
I THINK EVERYBODY NEEDS
TO KNOW THE TRUTH HERE.

26:06.083 --> 26:09.625
WE'RE FINE
WITH HOW THINGS ARE.
THEN I HAVE NO CHOICE.

26:09.667 --> 26:13.041
I HAVE TO REVEAL SOMETHING THAT,
LEGALLY, I'M NOT ALLOWED TO.
I THOUGHT WE WERE CLEAR
ABOUT THIS.

26:13.083 --> 26:15.583
COME ON, HONEY.
WE'RE GOING.
DEAN, YOUR PARENTS--

26:15.625 --> 26:17.667
STOP!
THIS IS NOT YOUR PLACE.

26:17.709 --> 26:19.709
THIS IS MY CHILD,
THIS IS MY LITTLE BOY,

26:19.750 --> 26:22.083
AND I WILL DO WHAT'S RIGHT.

26:22.125 --> 26:25.041
DEAN'S PLANNING ON HAVING SEX
WITH HIS GIRLFRIEND.

26:25.083 --> 26:27.625
(woman sobs)

26:27.667 --> 26:28.792
MOM.

26:28.834 --> 26:31.083
(woman) NO...

26:31.125 --> 26:33.750
I TRUSTED YOU.
WHY WOULD YOU DO THIS?

26:33.792 --> 26:37.667
WHY IS THIS SUCH A HUGE DEAL?
IT'S NOT THE END OF THE WORLD.

26:37.709 --> 26:39.250
WHAT'S GOING ON?

26:42.000 --> 26:43.959
DR. FREEDMAN,
COULD YOU STEP OUT?

26:44.000 --> 26:45.792
YEAH.

26:50.083 --> 26:52.041
(Addison) WHAT HAPPENED?

26:52.083 --> 26:54.041
SHE'S NOT DILATED
OR EFFACED,

26:54.083 --> 26:56.041
BUT HER WATER BROKE
AN HOUR AGO.

26:56.083 --> 26:57.667
PLUS, SHE'S BLEEDING,

26:57.709 --> 26:59.667
AND THE BABY'S SHOWING SIGNS
OF DISTRESS.

26:59.709 --> 27:01.750
I'VE GOTTA GET
THAT BABY OUT NOW.

27:01.792 --> 27:03.667
NAOMI, IF YOU COLLECT
THE CORD BLOOD,

27:03.709 --> 27:06.125
I HAVE A TEAM STANDING BY
READY TO TRANSPLANT.

27:06.166 --> 27:08.166
JASON'S PREPPED AND WAITING.
YEAH.

27:08.208 --> 27:10.291
WHAT DID YOU DO?
HER WATER JUST BROKE.

27:10.333 --> 27:13.709
I AM THE BEST CHANCE
YOUR BABY HAS OF SURVIVAL,

27:13.750 --> 27:16.041
BUT I WILL WALK OUT
OF THIS HOSPITAL RIGHT NOW

27:16.083 --> 27:18.041
AND LEAVE YOU, YOUR BABY
AND YOUR SON'S LIVES

27:18.083 --> 27:20.542
TO SOME NERVOUS O.B. RESIDENT
IF YOU LIE TO ME AGAIN.

27:20.583 --> 27:23.208
I AM SICK OF LIES.
WHAT DID YOU DO?

27:25.625 --> 27:28.583
I BROKE MY WATER MYSELF...

27:28.625 --> 27:31.750
WITH A KNITTING NEEDLE.

27:37.083 --> 27:38.583
(Addison) I NEED AN O.R.

27:38.625 --> 27:41.000
CALL ANESTHESIA,
MAKE SURE WE CAN GET A SPINAL,

27:41.041 --> 27:42.709
AND NOTIFY NICU

27:42.750 --> 27:45.291
WE'VE GOT A PREEMIE ON THE WAY.
LET'S GO, NOW.

27:48.875 --> 27:53.000
(monitor beeping rhythmically)

28:03.333 --> 28:05.542
IS THE BABY OKAY?

28:05.583 --> 28:08.000
TAKING OUT THE PLACENTA...

28:08.041 --> 28:10.125
AND THE UMBILICAL CORD.

28:10.166 --> 28:12.041
WHO'S CLOSING?
OVER HERE.

28:12.083 --> 28:14.166
GET IN HERE.

28:21.083 --> 28:22.583
(Molly sobs)

28:22.625 --> 28:24.583
IS THE BABY OKAY?

28:24.625 --> 28:27.667
APGAR'S 4. 3-0 E.T. TUBE
AND A STRAIGHT BLADE.
WAIT! IS THE BABY OKAY?

28:27.709 --> 28:30.625
NO. NO, SHE IS NOT OKAY.
PLEASE. I'M SORRY.

28:30.667 --> 28:33.125
PLEASE JUST SAVE HER.
PLEASE.

28:33.166 --> 28:36.250
I AM DOING EVERYTHING I CAN.

28:36.291 --> 28:39.041
(Naomi) MOLLY,
ERIC AND I ARE LEAVING.

28:39.083 --> 28:42.667
JASON SHOULD HAVE HIS FATHER
WITH HIM JUST IN CASE.
OKAY.

28:42.709 --> 28:45.000
(whimpers) I'M SORRY.

28:56.250 --> 28:58.667
OKAY, MAYBE WE SHOULD--

28:58.709 --> 29:01.917
STOP! ENOUGH!

29:01.959 --> 29:03.917
WHAT AM I GONNA TELL PEOPLE?

29:03.959 --> 29:07.709
"SORRY, I FORGOT
I HAVE A.I.D.S."?
YOU DON'T HAVE A.I.D.S.
OKAY, H.I.V.--

29:07.750 --> 29:09.709
H.I.V.--
YOU TAKE CARE OF YOURSELF,

29:09.750 --> 29:12.041
YOU'RE GONNA LIVE
A LONG, HEALTHY LIFE.

29:12.083 --> 29:14.792
YOU KNEW,
AND ALL THIS TIME,

29:14.834 --> 29:16.166
YOU DIDN'T TELL ME.

29:16.208 --> 29:18.917
I THOUGHT YOU WERE MY FRIEND.

29:18.959 --> 29:20.959
I COULDN'T TELL YOU
THE TRUTH BEFORE.

29:21.000 --> 29:23.875
AND NOW I WILL TELL YOU
EVERYTHING YOU NEED TO KNOW,

29:23.917 --> 29:25.875
AND I SWEAR...
I'LL DO EVERYTHING I CAN

29:25.917 --> 29:29.250
TO HELP YOU HAVE
THE LIFE YOU WANT.
BUT YOU CAN'T.
IT'S TOO LATE.

29:29.291 --> 29:32.542
WE HAD SEX LAST NIGHT.

29:32.583 --> 29:34.583
IT'S TOO LATE.

29:37.083 --> 29:40.041
CORD BLOOD'S ON ITS WAY
TO JASON AND...

29:40.083 --> 29:41.208
OH, DAMN.

29:41.250 --> 29:44.041
I'LL SEE IF I CAN GET
THE PARENTS UP HERE

29:44.083 --> 29:45.667
TO SAY GOOD-BYE
BEFORE SHE GOES.

29:45.709 --> 29:48.500
WAIT. WE'RE GONNA TRY
LIQUID VENTILATION ON HER.

29:48.542 --> 29:51.041
THAT'S HIGHLY EXPERIMENTAL.

29:51.083 --> 29:53.750
YES.
HAVE YOU EVER DONE IT
BEFORE?

29:53.792 --> 29:56.709
NO, BUT I'M ABOUT
TO DO IT NOW.

29:56.750 --> 29:59.709
THE FLUID EXPANDS HER LUGS
SO THEY DON'T COLLAPSE.

29:59.750 --> 30:01.875
WE'RE SIMULATING THE WOMB.
KEEP AN EYE ON HER SATs.

30:01.917 --> 30:04.542
IF THEY GO UP,
WE KNOW IT'S WORKING.

30:04.583 --> 30:06.750
(monitor beeps)

30:08.709 --> 30:11.041
(beep)

30:11.083 --> 30:14.625
(beeping increases)

30:16.917 --> 30:19.083
MONTGOMERY, SATs ARE FALLING.
GIVE ME A SECOND.

30:19.125 --> 30:21.041
(beeping continues)

30:21.083 --> 30:23.166
COME ON, COME ON.

30:23.208 --> 30:24.875
COME ON.

30:24.917 --> 30:27.250
(beeping continues)

30:27.291 --> 30:30.709
(beeping rhythmically)

30:32.750 --> 30:35.041
THERE WE GO.

30:35.083 --> 30:37.041
MONTGOMERY, WHERE THE HELL
HAVE YOU BEEN HIDING

30:37.083 --> 30:38.583
ALL MY MEDICAL LIFE?

30:38.625 --> 30:42.000
AWW, I LIKE YOU, TOO,
CHARLOTTE.

30:42.041 --> 30:45.000
♪♪

30:52.583 --> 30:56.000
♪♪

30:58.083 --> 31:00.917
HI. I CAME BY TO CHECK ON
THE MADISONS.

31:00.959 --> 31:03.041
HOW ARE THEY DOING?
MOM'S IN RECOVERY
FROM HER "C."

31:03.083 --> 31:04.959
JASON'S RECEIVING
HIS CORD BLOOD INFUSION.

31:05.000 --> 31:07.208
MONTGOMERY'S KEEPING
THE BABY ALIVE

31:07.250 --> 31:09.875
THROUGH SHEER FORCE OF WILL.
IT'S A MESS. (sighs)

31:09.917 --> 31:11.750
YOU EVER MISS
THE GOOD OLD DAYS,

31:11.792 --> 31:15.041
WHEN LIFE AND DEATH WAS DECIDED
BY GOD INSTEAD OF DOCTORS?

31:15.083 --> 31:17.041
WELL, WE'D BE OUT OF JOBS.
(laughs)

31:17.083 --> 31:19.667
BUT, MAN,
IT WOULD BE GOOD, THOUGH,

31:19.709 --> 31:23.208
TO JUST NOT BE IN CONTROL,
TO JUST LET GO, LET GOD.

31:23.250 --> 31:26.041
I COULD TRAVEL.
I COULD GO TO AFRICA.

31:26.083 --> 31:28.625
I COULD... TOUCH MONKEYS...

31:28.667 --> 31:30.542
OR WHATEVER.

31:30.583 --> 31:34.583
♪♪

31:38.959 --> 31:41.875
(monitor beeping rhythmically)

31:41.917 --> 31:44.917
♪♪

31:48.250 --> 31:51.667
HOW'S JASON?

31:51.709 --> 31:53.667
WE'LL SEE.

31:53.709 --> 31:55.250
HOW'S THE BABY?

31:55.291 --> 31:57.709
WE'LL SEE.

32:00.333 --> 32:02.041
THANK YOU.

32:02.083 --> 32:03.917
YEAH.

32:06.917 --> 32:08.291
THANK YOU.

32:08.333 --> 32:10.083
OKAY.

32:10.125 --> 32:12.083
YEAH.

32:12.125 --> 32:15.125
♪♪

32:20.291 --> 32:23.208
♪♪

32:23.250 --> 32:25.875
(Pete)
YOU DID THE RIGHT THING.

32:25.917 --> 32:29.667
I KNOW. (sighs)

32:29.709 --> 32:31.667
YOU DID WHAT YOU COULD.

32:31.709 --> 32:33.041
I KNOW.

32:36.083 --> 32:39.000
BUT THAT DOESN'T MAKE IT
ANY BETTER.

32:41.083 --> 32:43.000
NOPE.

32:43.041 --> 32:46.792
♪♪

32:46.834 --> 32:48.917
I HAVE TO TALK TO YOU.

32:48.959 --> 32:51.709
DELL, I DON'T HAVE TIME
FOR YOUR STUFF RIGHT NOW.

32:51.750 --> 32:55.291
IT'S GONNA HAVE TO WAIT.
YOU KNOW, I--I'VE BEEN COVERING
FOR YOU THE BEST THAT I CAN--

32:55.333 --> 32:57.291
THE BILLS, THE LATE NOTICES,
THE VENDOR CALLS.

32:57.333 --> 32:58.709
AND WHILE
YOU'RE WORKING OVERTIME

32:58.750 --> 33:01.041
TO STOP THE HEMORRHAGING,
I'VE BEEN TRYING TO CATCH

33:01.083 --> 33:03.542
THE THINGS YOU FORGET
AND THE STUFF YOU DON'T SEE.

33:03.583 --> 33:05.041
OKAY, I'VE BEEN
KEEPING YOUR SECRETS

33:05.083 --> 33:07.041
AND I HAVE BEEN HIDING
YOUR MISTAKES,

33:07.083 --> 33:09.250
AND I JUST WANTED TO SAY
SOMETHING SO I COULD HELP YOU.

33:09.291 --> 33:11.250
I-I THOUGHT THAT YOU--
I KNOW WHAT YOU THOUGHT.

33:11.291 --> 33:15.542
YOU THOUGHT I... YOU THOUGHT
I WANTED TO TALK ABOUT US.

33:15.583 --> 33:18.208
BUT I GET IT.
THERE IS NO US.

33:18.250 --> 33:22.041
SO, UM...
DAILY PATIENT SCHEDULES,

33:22.083 --> 33:26.291
PHONE SHEETS, VENDOR LISTS
AND MY KEYS TO THE OFFICES.

33:26.333 --> 33:29.625
DELL, WHAT...
I QUIT.

33:45.333 --> 33:47.625
(sighs)

34:00.792 --> 34:03.041
NAOMI'S RUNNING THE PRACTICE
INTO THE GROUND.

34:10.709 --> 34:12.041
(pen clatters)

34:12.083 --> 34:13.667
I WASN'T THINKING.

34:13.709 --> 34:16.583
(sighs)

34:16.625 --> 34:18.750
♪♪

34:18.792 --> 34:22.083
SOMETHING HAS TO BE DONE,
AND I CAN'T BE THE ONE TO DO IT.

34:22.125 --> 34:24.041
I'M NEW HERE.
I HAVEN'T EARNED THE RIGHT.

34:24.083 --> 34:26.041
AND SHE'S MY BEST FRIEND.

34:26.083 --> 34:28.041
WELL, I'M HER HUSBAND.

34:28.083 --> 34:29.208
WAS.

34:29.250 --> 34:32.041
I WAS HER HUSBAND.
NOW I'M NOT ANYTHING SO--

34:32.083 --> 34:34.041
SAM,
SOMETHING HAS TO BE DONE,

34:34.083 --> 34:36.875
AND YOU HAVE TO BE
THE ONE TO DO IT.

34:36.917 --> 34:39.792
♪♪

34:39.834 --> 34:42.000
YEAH.

34:42.041 --> 34:43.917
♪♪

34:43.959 --> 34:45.667
YOU'RE HERE LATE.

34:45.709 --> 34:48.041
I'M CATCHING UP
ON PATIENT NOTES.

34:48.083 --> 34:50.208
ME, TOO.

34:50.250 --> 34:55.041
♪♪

34:55.083 --> 34:56.542
WANT TO KNOW THE TRUTH?

34:56.583 --> 34:58.542
I'M TRYING TO REMEMBER
WHAT I DID

34:58.583 --> 35:00.625
BEFORE COOPER GOT A LIFE?

35:00.667 --> 35:02.542
IT'S RIDICULOUS.

35:02.583 --> 35:05.625
HE USED TO NEED ME,
AND NOW I NEED HIM.

35:05.667 --> 35:08.542
I'M TRYING TO FIGURE OUT
WHAT IT IS ABOUT ADDISON

35:08.583 --> 35:11.041
THAT MAKES ME ACT LIKE
A 14-YEAR-OLD BOY.

35:11.083 --> 35:13.041
IT'S HUMILIATING.

35:13.083 --> 35:15.709
I GOTTA START
SLEEPING AROUND AGAIN.

35:15.750 --> 35:19.041
DO YOU WANT TO COME
TO ZANZIBAR WITH ME?

35:19.083 --> 35:20.959
PRETTY GIRLS IN ZANZIBAR.

35:21.000 --> 35:22.625
I'VE BEEN.

35:22.667 --> 35:24.834
YOU CAN TOUCH MONKEYS THERE,
YOU KNOW.

35:24.875 --> 35:26.834
I KNEW IT.

35:26.875 --> 35:29.083
♪♪

35:29.125 --> 35:32.083
(rings doorbell)

35:32.125 --> 35:34.041
♪♪

35:34.083 --> 35:36.583
YOU CAN'T TELL ANYONE
ABOUT US.

35:36.625 --> 35:38.583
BUT I WILL CONSIDER A VACATION--
SOMEWHERE CLOSE,

35:38.625 --> 35:41.041
SOMEWHERE I CAN
FLEE FROM EASILY,

35:41.083 --> 35:43.625
LIKE NAPA OR PALM SPRINGS.

35:45.083 --> 35:47.542
I'M HERE.

35:47.583 --> 35:49.875
I CAME CRAWLIN' BACK, OKAY?

35:49.917 --> 35:52.041
I'M CRAWLIN'.
IN CROTCHLESS PANTIES?

35:52.083 --> 35:55.500
IN NO PANTIES.

35:55.542 --> 35:59.792
♪♪

35:59.834 --> 36:02.959
(doorbell rings)

36:03.000 --> 36:06.000
♪♪

36:08.333 --> 36:10.583
YOU KNOW WHERE I LIVE?

36:10.625 --> 36:13.041
I'M A COP. I-I KNOW
WHERE EVERYONE LIVES.

36:13.083 --> 36:15.208
(chuckles) FUNNY. UM...

36:15.250 --> 36:17.750
LISTEN, I HAVE HAD...

36:17.792 --> 36:20.041
THE WORST DAY, SO--

36:20.083 --> 36:22.041
WELL, WE COULD GO OUT.

36:22.083 --> 36:24.834
WE COULD GO OUT AND HAVE FUN
IN A CASUAL WAY

36:24.875 --> 36:26.959
THAT IS, UH, FUN AND CASUAL.

36:27.000 --> 36:29.041
I KNOW I'M SOME GUY
YOU BARELY KNOW,

36:29.083 --> 36:32.166
SOME TOTAL STRANGER WHO'S NOT
IN YOUR WORLD BUT I--

36:32.208 --> 36:36.208
NO, NO, THE "NOT
IN MY WORLD" PART IS GOOD.

36:36.250 --> 36:37.959
SO?

36:38.000 --> 36:42.041
♪♪

36:42.083 --> 36:44.542
SHOW ME THE S.W.A.T. THING
AGAIN.

36:44.583 --> 36:48.041
(laughs)

36:48.083 --> 36:50.041
♪♪

36:50.083 --> 36:54.041
(laughs)

36:54.083 --> 36:57.041
♪♪

36:57.083 --> 37:00.917
I JUST...

37:00.959 --> 37:03.875
I JUST...

37:03.917 --> 37:05.583
UH...

37:05.625 --> 37:08.750
I JUST WANT...

37:08.792 --> 37:11.000
CAN WE JUST BE US AGAIN?

37:11.041 --> 37:13.208
♪♪

37:13.250 --> 37:16.166
I JUST NEED SOMETHING
TO WORK.

37:16.208 --> 37:19.208
♪♪

37:28.625 --> 37:32.000
♪♪

37:39.125 --> 37:42.125
♪♪

37:51.083 --> 37:53.083
DELL!

37:53.125 --> 37:55.125
(elevator bell dings)

38:00.750 --> 38:03.208
(Dean)
THIS IS MY GIRLFRIEND AMY.

38:03.250 --> 38:05.834
WHAT YOU SAID YESTERDAY
ABOUT ANSWERING QUESTIONS...

38:05.875 --> 38:07.792
WE HAVE A LOT.

38:07.834 --> 38:11.000
WELL, WHY DON'T YOU ALL
COME INTO MY OFFICE?

38:20.083 --> 38:22.000
THANK YOU.

38:24.083 --> 38:26.083
DR. MONTGOMERY.

